FilterProperty.name: filter
FilterProperty.summary: The filter CSS property applies graphical effects like blur or color shift to an element. Filters are commonly used to adjust the rendering of images, backgrounds, and borders.

chrome.notes: In Chrome 18 to 19, the saturate() function only takes integers instead of decimal or percentage values. From Chrome 20, this bug is fixed.

ie.notes: Internet Explorer 4 to 9 implemented a non-standard filter property. The syntax was completely different from this one and is not documented here.

edge_blink.notes: In Chrome 18 to 19, the saturate() function only takes integers instead of decimal or percentage values. From Chrome 20, this bug is fixed.

FilterProperty.title: filter

FilterProperty.name: filter
FilterProperty.summary: The filter attribute specifies the filter effects defined by the <filter> element that shall be applied to its element.
FilterProperty.title: filter

funcdef-filter-blur.name: blur
funcdef-filter-blur.summary: The blur() CSS function applies a Gaussian blur to the input image. Its result is a <filter-function>.
funcdef-filter-blur.title: blur()

funcdef-filter-brightness.name: brightness
funcdef-filter-brightness.summary: The brightness() CSS function applies a linear multiplier to the input image, making it appear brighter or darker. Its result is a <filter-function>.
funcdef-filter-brightness.title: brightness()

funcdef-filter-contrast.name: contrast
funcdef-filter-contrast.summary: The contrast() CSS function adjusts the contrast of the input image. Its result is a <filter-function>.
funcdef-filter-contrast.title: contrast()

funcdef-filter-drop-shadow.name: drop-shadow
funcdef-filter-drop-shadow.summary: The drop-shadow() CSS function applies a drop shadow effect to the input image. Its result is a <filter-function>.
funcdef-filter-drop-shadow.title: drop-shadow()

funcdef-filter-grayscale.name: grayscale
funcdef-filter-grayscale.summary: The grayscale() CSS function converts the input image to grayscale. Its result is a <filter-function>.
funcdef-filter-grayscale.title: grayscale()

funcdef-filter-hue-rotate.name: hue-rotate
funcdef-filter-hue-rotate.summary: The hue-rotate() CSS function rotates the hue of an element and its contents. Its result is a <filter-function>.
funcdef-filter-hue-rotate.title: hue-rotate()

funcdef-filter-invert.name: invert
funcdef-filter-invert.summary: The invert() CSS function inverts the color samples in the input image. Its result is a <filter-function>.
funcdef-filter-invert.title: invert()

funcdef-filter-opacity.name: opacity
funcdef-filter-opacity.summary: The opacity() CSS function applies transparency to the samples in the input image. Its result is a <filter-function>.
funcdef-filter-opacity.title: opacity()

funcdef-filter-saturate.name: saturate
funcdef-filter-saturate.summary: The saturate() CSS function super-saturates or desaturates the input image. Its result is a <filter-function>.
funcdef-filter-saturate.title: saturate()

funcdef-filter-sepia.name: sepia
funcdef-filter-sepia.summary: The sepia() CSS function converts the input image to sepia, giving it a warmer, more yellow/brown appearance. Its result is a <filter-function>.
funcdef-filter-sepia.title: sepia()

typedef-filter-function.name: filter-function
typedef-filter-function.summary: The <filter-function> CSS data type represents a graphical effect that can change the appearance of an input image. It is used in the filter and backdrop-filter properties.
typedef-filter-function.title: <filter-function>

element-attrdef-feimage-href.name: href
element-attrdef-feimage-href.summary: The href attribute defines a link to a resource as a reference URL. The exact meaning of that link depends on the context of each element using it.
element-attrdef-feimage-href.title: href

ColorInterpolationFiltersProperty.name: color-interpolation-filters
ColorInterpolationFiltersProperty.summary: The color-interpolation-filters attribute specifies the color space for imaging operations performed via filter effects.
ColorInterpolationFiltersProperty.title: color-interpolation-filters

FloodColorProperty.name: flood-color
FloodColorProperty.summary: The flood-color attribute indicates what color to use to flood the current filter primitive subregion.
FloodColorProperty.title: flood-color

FloodOpacityProperty.name: flood-opacity
FloodOpacityProperty.summary: The flood-opacity attribute indicates the opacity value to use across the current filter primitive subregion.
FloodOpacityProperty.title: flood-opacity

LightingColorProperty.name: lighting-color
LightingColorProperty.summary: The lighting-color attribute defines the color of the light source for lighting filter primitives.
LightingColorProperty.title: lighting-color

element-attrdef-feblend-mode.name: mode
element-attrdef-feblend-mode.summary: The mode attribute defines the blending mode on the <feBlend> filter primitive.
element-attrdef-feblend-mode.title: mode

feBlendElement.name: feBlend
feBlendElement.summary: The <feBlend> SVG filter primitive composes two objects together ruled by a certain blending mode. This is similar to what is known from image editing software when blending two layers. The mode is defined by the mode attribute.
feBlendElement.title: <feBlend>

feColorMatrixElement.name: feColorMatrix
feColorMatrixElement.summary: The <feColorMatrix> SVG filter element changes colors based on a transformation matrix. Every pixel's color value [R,G,B,A] is matrix multiplied by a 5 by 5 color matrix to create new color [R',G',B',A'].
feColorMatrixElement.title: <feColorMatrix>

feComponentTransferElement.name: feComponentTransfer
feComponentTransferElement.summary: The <feComponentTransfer> SVG filter primitive performs color-component-wise remapping of data for each pixel. It allows operations like brightness adjustment, contrast adjustment, color balance or thresholding.
feComponentTransferElement.title: <feComponentTransfer>

element-attrdef-fecomposite-k1.name: k1
element-attrdef-fecomposite-k1.summary: The k1 attribute defines one of the values to be used within the arithmetic operation of the <feComposite> filter primitive.
element-attrdef-fecomposite-k1.title: k1

element-attrdef-fecomposite-k2.name: k2
element-attrdef-fecomposite-k2.summary: The k2 attribute defines one of the values to be used within the arithmetic operation of the <feComposite> filter primitive.
element-attrdef-fecomposite-k2.title: k2

element-attrdef-fecomposite-k3.name: k3
element-attrdef-fecomposite-k3.summary: The k3 attribute defines one of the values to be used within the arithmetic operation of the <feComposite> filter primitive.
element-attrdef-fecomposite-k3.title: k3

element-attrdef-fecomposite-k4.name: k4
element-attrdef-fecomposite-k4.summary: The k4 attribute defines one of the values to be used within the arithmetic operation of the <feComposite> filter primitive.
element-attrdef-fecomposite-k4.title: k4

feCompositeElement.name: feComposite
feCompositeElement.summary: The <feComposite> SVG filter primitive performs the combination of two input images pixel-wise in image space using one of the Porter-Duff compositing operations: over, in, atop, out, xor, lighter, or arithmetic.
feCompositeElement.title: <feComposite>

element-attrdef-feconvolvematrix-bias.name: bias
element-attrdef-feconvolvematrix-bias.summary: The bias attribute shifts the range of the filter. After applying the kernelMatrix of the <feConvolveMatrix> element to the input image to yield a number and applied the divisor attribute, the bias attribute is added to each component. This allows representation of values that would otherwise be clamped to 0 or 1.
element-attrdef-feconvolvematrix-bias.title: bias

element-attrdef-feconvolvematrix-divisor.name: divisor
element-attrdef-feconvolvematrix-divisor.summary: The divisor attribute specifies the value by which the resulting number of applying the kernelMatrix of a <feConvolveMatrix> element to the input image color value is divided to yield the destination color value.
element-attrdef-feconvolvematrix-divisor.title: divisor

element-attrdef-feconvolvematrix-edgemod.name: edgeMode
element-attrdef-feconvolvematrix-edgemod.summary: The edgeMode attribute determines how to extend the input image as necessary with color values so that the matrix operations can be applied when the kernel is positioned at or near the edge of the input image.
element-attrdef-feconvolvematrix-edgemod.title: edgeMode

element-attrdef-filter-primitive-in.name: in
element-attrdef-filter-primitive-in.summary: The in attribute identifies input for the given filter primitive.
element-attrdef-filter-primitive-in.title: in

element-attrdef-filter-primitive-in.name: in
element-attrdef-filter-primitive-in.summary: The in attribute identifies input for the given filter primitive.
element-attrdef-filter-primitive-in.title: in

element-attrdef-feconvolvematrix-kernelm.name: kernelMatrix
element-attrdef-feconvolvematrix-kernelm.summary: The kernelMatrix attribute defines the list of numbers that make up the kernel matrix for the <feConvolveMatrix> element.
element-attrdef-feconvolvematrix-kernelm.title: kernelMatrix

element-attrdef-feconvolvematrix-kernelu.name: kernelUnitLength
element-attrdef-feconvolvematrix-kernelu.summary: The kernelUnitLength attribute has two meanings based on the context it's used in. For lighting filter primitives, it indicates the intended distance for the x and y coordinates, for <feConvolveMatrix>, it indicates the intended distance between successive columns and rows in the kernel matrix.
element-attrdef-feconvolvematrix-kernelu.title: kernelUnitLength

element-attrdef-order.name: order
element-attrdef-order.summary: The order attribute indicates the size of the matrix to be used by a <feConvolveMatrix> element.
element-attrdef-order.title: order

element-attrdef-feconvolvematrix-preserv.name: preserveAlpha
element-attrdef-feconvolvematrix-preserv.summary: the preserveAlpha attribute indicates how a <feConvolveMatrix> element handled alpha transparency.
element-attrdef-feconvolvematrix-preserv.title: preserveAlpha

element-attrdef-feconvolvematrix-targetx.name: targetX
element-attrdef-feconvolvematrix-targetx.summary: The targetX attribute determines the positioning in horizontal direction of the convolution matrix relative to a given target pixel in the input image. The leftmost column of the matrix is column number zero. The value must be such that: 0 <= targetX < order X.
element-attrdef-feconvolvematrix-targetx.title: targetX

element-attrdef-feconvolvematrix-targety.name: targetY
element-attrdef-feconvolvematrix-targety.summary: The targetY attribute determines the positioning in vertical direction of the convolution matrix relative to a given target pixel in the input image. The topmost row of the matrix is row number zero. The value must be such that: 0 <= targetY < order Y.
element-attrdef-feconvolvematrix-targety.title: targetY

feConvolveMatrixElement.name: feConvolveMatrix
feConvolveMatrixElement.summary: The <feConvolveMatrix> SVG filter primitive applies a matrix convolution filter effect. A convolution combines pixels in the input image with neighboring pixels to produce a resulting image. A wide variety of imaging operations can be achieved through convolutions, including blurring, edge detection, sharpening, embossing and beveling.
feConvolveMatrixElement.title: <feConvolveMatrix>

element-attrdef-fediffuselighting-diffus.name: diffuseConstant
element-attrdef-fediffuselighting-diffus.summary: The diffuseConstant attribute represents the kd value in the Phong lighting model. In SVG, this can be any non-negative number.
element-attrdef-fediffuselighting-diffus.title: diffuseConstant

element-attrdef-fediffuselighting-kernel.name: kernelUnitLength
element-attrdef-fediffuselighting-kernel.summary: The kernelUnitLength attribute has two meanings based on the context it's used in. For lighting filter primitives, it indicates the intended distance for the x and y coordinates, for <feConvolveMatrix>, it indicates the intended distance between successive columns and rows in the kernel matrix.
element-attrdef-fediffuselighting-kernel.title: kernelUnitLength

element-attrdef-fediffuselighting-surfac.name: surfaceScale
element-attrdef-fediffuselighting-surfac.summary: The surfaceScale attribute represents the height of the surface for a light filter primitive.
element-attrdef-fediffuselighting-surfac.title: surfaceScale

feDiffuseLightingElement.name: feDiffuseLighting
feDiffuseLightingElement.summary: The <feDiffuseLighting> SVG filter primitive lights an image using the alpha channel as a bump map. The resulting image, which is an RGBA opaque image, depends on the light color, light position and surface geometry of the input bump map.
feDiffuseLightingElement.title: <feDiffuseLighting>

element-attrdef-fedisplacementmap-scale.name: scale
element-attrdef-fedisplacementmap-scale.summary: The scale attribute defines the displacement scale factor to be used on a <feDisplacementMap> filter primitive. The amount is expressed in the coordinate system established by the primitiveUnits attribute on the <filter> element.
element-attrdef-fedisplacementmap-scale.title: scale

element-attrdef-fedisplacementmap-xchann.name: xChannelSelector
element-attrdef-fedisplacementmap-xchann.summary: The xChannelSelector attribute indicates which color channel from in2 to use to displace the pixels in in along the x-axis.
element-attrdef-fedisplacementmap-xchann.title: xChannelSelector

element-attrdef-fedisplacementmap-ychann.name: yChannelSelector
element-attrdef-fedisplacementmap-ychann.summary: The yChannelSelector attribute indicates which color channel from in2 to use to displace the pixels in in along the y-axis.
element-attrdef-fedisplacementmap-ychann.title: yChannelSelector

feDisplacementMapElement.name: feDisplacementMap
feDisplacementMapElement.summary: The <feDisplacementMap> SVG filter primitive uses the pixel values from the image from in2 to spatially displace the image from in.
feDisplacementMapElement.title: <feDisplacementMap>

element-attrdef-fedistantlight-azimuth.name: azimuth
element-attrdef-fedistantlight-azimuth.summary: The azimuth attribute specifies the direction angle for the light source on the XY plane (clockwise), in degrees from the x axis.
element-attrdef-fedistantlight-azimuth.title: azimuth

element-attrdef-fedistantlight-elevation.name: elevation
element-attrdef-fedistantlight-elevation.summary: The elevation attribute specifies the direction angle for the light source from the XY plane towards the Z-axis, in degrees. Note that the positive Z-axis points towards the viewer of the content.
element-attrdef-fedistantlight-elevation.title: elevation

feDistantLightElement.name: feDistantLight
feDistantLightElement.summary: The <feDistantLight> filter primitive defines a distant light source that can be used within a lighting filter primitive: <feDiffuseLighting> or <feSpecularLighting>.
feDistantLightElement.title: <feDistantLight>

feDropShadowElement.name: feDropShadow
feDropShadowElement.summary: The SVG <feDropShadow> filter primitive creates a drop shadow of the input image. It can only be used inside a <filter> element.
feDropShadowElement.title: <feDropShadow>

feFloodElement.name: feFlood
feFloodElement.summary: The <feFlood> SVG filter primitive fills the filter subregion with the color and opacity defined by flood-color and flood-opacity.
feFloodElement.title: <feFlood>

feFuncAElement.name: feFuncA
feFuncAElement.summary: The <feFuncA> SVG filter primitive defines the transfer function for the alpha component of the input graphic of its parent <feComponentTransfer> element.
feFuncAElement.title: <feFuncA>

feFuncBElement.name: feFuncB
feFuncBElement.summary: The <feFuncB> SVG filter primitive defines the transfer function for the blue component of the input graphic of its parent <feComponentTransfer> element.
feFuncBElement.title: <feFuncB>

feFuncGElement.name: feFuncG
feFuncGElement.summary: The <feFuncG> SVG filter primitive defines the transfer function for the green component of the input graphic of its parent <feComponentTransfer> element.
feFuncGElement.title: <feFuncG>

feFuncRElement.name: feFuncR
feFuncRElement.summary: The <feFuncR> SVG filter primitive defines the transfer function for the red component of the input graphic of its parent <feComponentTransfer> element.
feFuncRElement.title: <feFuncR>

element-attrdef-fegaussianblur-stddeviat.name: stdDeviation
element-attrdef-fegaussianblur-stddeviat.summary: The stdDeviation attribute defines the standard deviation for the blur operation.
element-attrdef-fegaussianblur-stddeviat.title: stdDeviation

feGaussianBlurElement.name: feGaussianBlur
feGaussianBlurElement.summary: The <feGaussianBlur> SVG filter primitive blurs the input image by the amount specified in stdDeviation, which defines the bell-curve.
feGaussianBlurElement.title: <feGaussianBlur>

feImageElement.name: feImage
feImageElement.summary: The <feImage> SVG filter primitive fetches image data from an external source and provides the pixel data as output (meaning if the external source is an SVG image, it is rasterized.)
feImageElement.title: <feImage>

feMergeElement.name: feMerge
feMergeElement.summary: The <feMerge> SVG element allows filter effects to be applied concurrently instead of sequentially. This is achieved by other filters storing their output via the result attribute and then accessing it in a <feMergeNode> child.
feMergeElement.title: <feMerge>

feMergeNodeElement.name: feMergeNode
feMergeNodeElement.summary: The feMergeNode takes the result of another filter to be processed by its parent <feMerge>.
feMergeNodeElement.title: <feMergeNode>

element-attrdef-femorphology-radius.name: radius
element-attrdef-femorphology-radius.summary: The radius attribute represents the radius (or radii) for the operation on a given <feMorphology> filter primitive.
element-attrdef-femorphology-radius.title: radius

feMorphologyElement.name: feMorphology
feMorphologyElement.summary: The <feMorphology> SVG filter primitive is used to erode or dilate the input image. Its usefulness lies especially in fattening or thinning effects.
feMorphologyElement.title: <feMorphology>

feOffsetElement.name: feOffset
feOffsetElement.summary: The <feOffset> SVG filter primitive allows to offset the input image. The input image as a whole is offset by the values specified in the dx and dy attributes.
feOffsetElement.title: <feOffset>

fePointLightElement.name: fePointLight
fePointLightElement.summary: The <fePointLight> filter primitive defines a light source which allows to create a point light effect. It that can be used within a lighting filter primitive: <feDiffuseLighting> or <feSpecularLighting>.
fePointLightElement.title: <fePointLight>

element-attrdef-fespecularlighting-specu.name: specularConstant
element-attrdef-fespecularlighting-specu.summary: The specularConstant attribute controls the ratio of reflection of the specular lighting. It represents the ks value in the Phong lighting model. The bigger the value the stronger the reflection.
element-attrdef-fespecularlighting-specu.title: specularConstant

feSpecularLightingElement.name: feSpecularLighting
feSpecularLightingElement.summary: The <feSpecularLighting> SVG filter primitive lights a source graphic using the alpha channel as a bump map. The resulting image is an RGBA image based on the light color. The lighting calculation follows the standard specular component of the Phong lighting model. The resulting image depends on the light color, light position and surface geometry of the input bump map. The result of the lighting calculation is added. The filter primitive assumes that the viewer is at infinity in the z direction.
feSpecularLightingElement.title: <feSpecularLighting>

element-attrdef-fespotlight-limitingcone.name: limitingConeAngle
element-attrdef-fespotlight-limitingcone.summary: The limitingConeAngle attribute represents the angle in degrees between the spot light axis (i.e. the axis between the light source and the point to which it is pointing at) and the spot light cone. So it defines a limiting cone which restricts the region where the light is projected. No light is projected outside the cone.
element-attrdef-fespotlight-limitingcone.title: limitingConeAngle

element-attrdef-fespotlight-pointsatx.name: pointsAtX
element-attrdef-fespotlight-pointsatx.summary: The pointsAtX attribute represents the x location in the coordinate system established by attribute primitiveUnits on the <filter> element of the point at which the light source is pointing.
element-attrdef-fespotlight-pointsatx.title: pointsAtX

element-attrdef-fespotlight-pointsaty.name: pointsAtY
element-attrdef-fespotlight-pointsaty.summary: The pointsAtY attribute represents the y location in the coordinate system established by attribute primitiveUnits on the <filter> element of the point at which the light source is pointing.
element-attrdef-fespotlight-pointsaty.title: pointsAtY

element-attrdef-fespotlight-pointsatz.name: pointsAtZ
element-attrdef-fespotlight-pointsatz.summary: The pointsAtZ attribute represents the y location in the coordinate system established by attribute primitiveUnits on the <filter> element of the point at which the light source is pointing, assuming that, in the initial local coordinate system, the positive z-axis comes out towards the person viewing the content and assuming that one unit along the z-axis equals one unit in x and y.
element-attrdef-fespotlight-pointsatz.title: pointsAtZ

feSpotLightElement.name: feSpotLight
feSpotLightElement.summary: The <feSpotLight> SVG filter primitive defines a light source that can be used to create a spotlight effect. It is used within a lighting filter primitive: <feDiffuseLighting> or <feSpecularLighting>.
feSpotLightElement.title: <feSpotLight>

feTileElement.name: feTile
feTileElement.summary: The <feTile> SVG filter primitive allows to fill a target rectangle with a repeated, tiled pattern of an input image. The effect is similar to the one of a <pattern>.
feTileElement.title: <feTile>

element-attrdef-feturbulence-basefrequen.name: baseFrequency
element-attrdef-feturbulence-basefrequen.summary: The baseFrequency attribute represents the base frequency parameter for the noise function of the <feTurbulence> filter primitive.
element-attrdef-feturbulence-basefrequen.title: baseFrequency

element-attrdef-feturbulence-numoctaves.name: numOctaves
element-attrdef-feturbulence-numoctaves.summary: The numOctaves attribute defines the number of octaves for the noise function of the <feTurbulence> primitive.
element-attrdef-feturbulence-numoctaves.title: numOctaves

element-attrdef-feturbulence-seed.name: seed
element-attrdef-feturbulence-seed.summary: The seed attribute represents the starting number for the pseudo random number generator of the <feTurbulence> filter primitive.
element-attrdef-feturbulence-seed.title: seed

element-attrdef-feturbulence-stitchtiles.name: stitchTiles
element-attrdef-feturbulence-stitchtiles.summary: The stitchTiles attribute defines how the Perlin Noise tiles behave at the border.
element-attrdef-feturbulence-stitchtiles.title: stitchTiles

element-attrdef-feturbulence-type.name: type
element-attrdef-feturbulence-type.summary: The type attribute is a generic attribute and it has different meaning based on the context in which it's used.
element-attrdef-feturbulence-type.title: type

feTurbulenceElement.name: feTurbulence
feTurbulenceElement.summary: The <feTurbulence> SVG filter primitive creates an image using the Perlin turbulence function. It allows the synthesis of artificial textures like clouds or marble. The resulting image will fill the entire filter primitive subregion.
feTurbulenceElement.title: <feTurbulence>

element-attrdef-filter-filterunits.name: filterUnits
element-attrdef-filter-filterunits.summary: The filterUnits attribute defines the coordinate system for the attributes x, y, width and height.
element-attrdef-filter-filterunits.title: filterUnits

element-attrdef-filter-height.name: height
element-attrdef-filter-height.summary: The height attribute defines the vertical length of an element in the user coordinate system.
element-attrdef-filter-height.title: height

element-attrdef-filter-primitiveunits.name: primitiveUnits
element-attrdef-filter-primitiveunits.summary: The primitiveUnits attribute specifies the coordinate system for the various length values within the filter primitives and for the attributes that define the filter primitive subregion.
element-attrdef-filter-primitiveunits.title: primitiveUnits

element-attrdef-filter-width.name: width
element-attrdef-filter-width.summary: The width attribute defines the horizontal length of an element in the user coordinate system.
element-attrdef-filter-width.title: width

element-attrdef-filter-x.name: x
element-attrdef-filter-x.summary: The x attribute defines an x-axis coordinate in the user coordinate system.
element-attrdef-filter-x.title: x

element-attrdef-filter-y.name: y
element-attrdef-filter-y.summary: The y attribute defines a y-axis coordinate in the user coordinate system.
element-attrdef-filter-y.title: y

FilterElement.name: filter
FilterElement.summary: The <filter> SVG element defines a custom filter effect by grouping atomic filter primitives. It is never rendered itself, but must be used by the filter attribute on SVG elements, or the filter CSS property for SVG/HTML elements.
FilterElement.title: <filter>
